Penta1 volumes stayed close to expected through 2025, with only minor deviations. In June, ~28,900 doses (~7% above expected) reflected stable alignment with trend rather than a major surplus. Strengthening this early dose remains key for continuity of the series.

Penta3 volumes mostly tracked expectations but surged in late 2024 (+11–15%) and April 2025 (+14%), likely from catch-up or campaigns. By June, ~26,500 doses (~4% above expected) signaled a return to stable trend."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2562c43a-1b26-48a3-a872-b9740f37af04","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Immunization services strengthen in 2025, with gains in BCG and Penta3"}}

